"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427028","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-18","<p>The Government is working closely with the Greater Manchester Combined Authority on the implementation of the landmark agreement to introduce a metro-wide Mayor. Culture is a key element of building a Northern Powerhouse. The Government has committed to support arts and cultural projects in Greater Manchester, including £78 million towards a new theatre and exhibition space called The Factory Manchester, and £3 million for a new temporary exhibition space at Manchester’s Museum of Science and Industry.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-11-18T16:13:42.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427028/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427028/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427028/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-09","Arts: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the leaders of the Greater Manchester Combined Authority on future provision of funding for the arts after the devolution agreement comes into effect.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","15640"
