"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427302","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The information requested regarding the number and proportion of people who made a claim for support for mortgage interest between 1995 and 2009 who went into arrears on the interest or capital repayment during the waiting period is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-16T17:09:40.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427302/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427302/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people who made a claim for support for mortgage interest in each year between 1995 and 2009 went into arrears on their (a) interest repayments and (b) capital repayments (i) during the first 13 weeks of the waiting period and (ii) between weeks 13 and 39 of the waiting period.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427303","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The information requested regarding the number and proportion of people who made a claim for support for mortgage interest from 2009 to date who were in arrears on the interest or capital repayment during their waiting period is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-16T16:56:26.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427303/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427303/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people who made a claim for support for mortgage interest in (a) 2009-10, (b) 2010-11, (c) 2011-12, (d) 2012-13, (e) 2013-14 and (f) 2014-15 went into arrears on their (i) interest repayments and (ii) capital repayments during the 13-week waiting period.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427304","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-17","<p>The information is not available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-17T16:04:51.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427304/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427304/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people in receipt of support for mortgage interest who were also in receipt of income-based jobseeker's allowance, reached the end of the two-year limit in (a) 2009-10, (b) 2010-11, (c) 2011-12, (d) 2012-13, (e) 2013-14 and (f) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427305","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-17","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p>Universal Credit (UC) does not currently accept claims from owner occupiers. Once this claimant group starts claiming UC we expect that the numbers of any potential owner occupiers making a claim to be small.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-17T16:15:53.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427305/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427305/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Universal Credit: Mortgages","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people in receipt of universal credit receive help with mortgage costs.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427306","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-17","<p>The information requested is in the table:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of SMI claims</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>As % of all SMI claims</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Jobseekers allowance</strong></p></td><td><p>16,000</p></td><td><p>10%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Employment and support allowance</strong></p></td><td><p>56,000</p></td><td><p>34%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Income support</strong></p></td><td><p>24,000</p></td><td><p>14%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Pension credit</strong></p></td><td><p>71,000</p></td><td><p>43%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>167,000</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*The percentages may not sum to 100% due to rounding</p><br /><p>These figures are from the DWP summer budget 2015 benefit expenditure and caseload tables, which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2015</a></p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-17T16:26:40.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427306/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427306/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people who are in receipt of support for mortgage interest are also in receipt of (a) income-based jobseeker's allowance, (b) income-based employment and support allowance, (c) income support and (d) pension credit.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427307","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Government will not be revisiting the State Pension age arrangements for women affected by the Pensions Act 1995 and Pensions Act 2011. These women will receive their State Pension either at the same age as men or earlier as we remove current gender timetable inequality.</p><br /><p>The equalisation of State Pension age was necessary to meet the UK’s obligations under EU law to eliminate gender inequalities in social security provision. The Pensions Act 1995 contained legislation to equalise women’s State Pension age and, since April 2010, women’s State Pension age has been gradually increasing. Following sharp increases in life expectancy projections, and therefore the increase in the number of people living longer in retirement, this timetable was accelerated by the Pensions Act 2011.</p><br /><p>A concession was made prior to the passing of the 2011 Act which reduced the delay that anyone would experience in claiming their State Pension, relative to the previous timetable, to 18 months. This concession benefited almost a quarter of a million women, who would otherwise have experienced delays of up to two years. A similar number of men also benefited from a reduced increase, and the concession was worth around £1 billion in total.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","15639","2015-11-20T14:55:38.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427307/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427307/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will provide support for women who have been affected financially  as a result of changes brought about by the Pension Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","15476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427308","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-19","<p>Information on the average amount foregone by women who will wait longer to receive their state pension as a result of changes brought about by the Pensions Act 2011 is not available.</p><br /><p>The impact on total lifetime pension income depends on income level, and whether an individual works up to their new State Pension age. The Pensions Act 2011 Impact Assessment presents modelled impacts using hypothetical examples of single individual male and female high, median and low earners. This analysis focuses on illustrating the impact on income in retirement. It therefore does not take account of gains in working-life income through earnings (or working-age benefits) received in the period up to the new State Pension age that will either wholly or partially replace the income a person would have received from their private and / or State Pensions.</p><br /><p>The Pensions Act 2011 Impact Assessment, published in November 2011, is available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/181462/pensions-bill-2011-ia-annexa.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/181462/pensions-bill-2011-ia-annexa.pdf</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-19T13:27:32.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427308/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427308/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average amount foregone by women who will wait longer to receive their state pension was as a result of changes brought about by the Pension Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","15477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427309","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>Benefit off-flow data is not used to calculate increases to consolidated pay.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T12:07:13.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427309/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427309/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Jobcentre Plus: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how his Department has used benefit off-flow data in the last three years to calculate remuneration for jobcentre (a) managers and (b) advisers.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","15541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427310","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>Allegations of misuse of the Flexible Support Fund at Plaistow Jobcentre were investigated fully by the Department’s professionally trained investigators. It is not appropriate for the Secretary of State to disclose detailed information about internal investigations as providing this information would risk individuals being identified.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T12:09:59.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427310/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427310/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) advisers and (b) managers were interviewed during the course of the investigation which led to the dismissal of two advisers at Plaistow Jobcentre in May 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","15542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427311","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The impact on work incentives of the 65% taper was set out in the 2012 Universal Credit (UC) Impact Assessment (see link below).</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220177/universal-credit-wr2011-ia.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220177/universal-credit-wr2011-ia.pdf</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T16:08:00.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427311/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427311/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of an increase in the universal credit taper rate on (a) work incentives and (b) progression incentives.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","15543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427312","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The information is in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td>Year</td><td>Number of Advisers that worked at Plaistow Jobcentre</td></tr><tr><td>2010/11</td><td>24</td></tr><tr><td>2011/12</td><td>26</td></tr><tr><td>2012/13</td><td>27</td></tr><tr><td>2013/14</td><td>23</td></tr><tr><td>2014/15</td><td>27</td></tr></tbody></table><p>1. Source of management information: DWP Work Services Activity Based Management Tool</p><p>2. The management information is collated and reported for the period from April to March for each year</p><p>3. The numbers of advisers are expressed as Full Time Equivalents</p><p>4. The management information contained within this document does not form part of any official statistics and is intended for DWP internal use only.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T12:17:35.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427312/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427312/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many advisers worked at Plaistow Jobcentre in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","15544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427313","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answers I gave on 3 November 2015 to Question 14114 and 14139</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T12:16:30.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427313/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427313/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Jobcentre Plus: Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to roll-out the placement of Jobcentre Plus advisers in food banks.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","15545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427314","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>In May 2015, about 48% of the 460,000 claimants in the work-related activity group receive both ESA and PIP/DLA.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T14:44:26.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427314/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427314/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 14 October 2015 to Question 10742, what proportion of people in the work-related activity group of employment and support allowance are also in receipt of personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","15487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427315","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>DWP have made no assessment of the provision of free childcare on productivity itself. However, several reports, including the DWP working paper A Survey of Childcare and Work Decisions among Families with Children, identify childcare costs as one of the main barriers to returning to work after the birth of a child. ONS data show women with young children have lower employment rates than men, and the Resolution Foundation reports that mothers who are employed are more likely to have part time and low-paid jobs due to childcare responsibilities. Provision of free childcare should support mothers to combine high-skilled and full time work with raising children.</p><p>Also, evidence from the IFS report The Economic Effects of Pre-school Education and Quality suggests that children who have attended pre-school earn more over their working lives on average than children who have had little or no pre-schooling.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-16T16:35:12.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427315/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427315/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the contribution of the provision of free childcare to UK productivity in (a) 2005-2010, (b) 2010-2015 and (c) 2015-2020.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","15449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427316","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The full information requested is not held centrally.</p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions checks the nationality and immigration status of benefit claimants to ensure the benefit is paid properly and to prevent fraud. While this information is used, it is not recorded as part of the benefit payment administrative systems.</p><p>Benefit Expenditure and Caseload tables are published on Gov.UK. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/474453/expenditure-by-country-and-region-2014-15.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/474453/expenditure-by-country-and-region-2014-15.xlsx</a></p><p>Please note that these figures include a breakdown for UK regions and a combined figure for expenditure abroad or where the region is unknown. Expenditure is not broken down by nationality.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","15455","2015-11-16T14:46:55.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427316/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427316/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Social Security Benefits: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent from the public purse on the payment of social security benefits to non-UK citizens in each European Economic Area country for each year from 1997-98 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427317","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-16","<p>The full information requested is not held centrally.</p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions checks the nationality and immigration status of benefit claimants to ensure the benefit is paid properly and to prevent fraud. While this information is used, it is not recorded as part of the benefit payment administrative systems.</p><p>Benefit Expenditure and Caseload tables are published on Gov.UK. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/474453/expenditure-by-country-and-region-2014-15.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/474453/expenditure-by-country-and-region-2014-15.xlsx</a></p><p>Please note that these figures include a breakdown for UK regions and a combined figure for expenditure abroad or where the region is unknown. Expenditure is not broken down by nationality.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","15457","2015-11-16T14:46:55.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427317/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427317/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","Social Security Benefits: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent from the public purse on the payment of social security benefits to non-UK citizens in each non-European Economic Area country for each year from 1997-98 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427318","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-20","<p>Entitlement to UK State Pension is based on UK national insurance contributions and credits which enables pensioners, many of whom are UK nationals, to receive their state pensions abroad.</p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not hold data on the nationality of State Pension claimants however;</p><p>State Pension expenditure by country of residence is published on Gov.UK <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/464096/state-pension-by-country-2014-15.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/464096/state-pension-by-country-2014-15.xlsx</a>.</p><p>Expenditure is not broken down by nationality.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","15453","2015-11-20T14:58:51.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427318/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427318/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-09","State Retirement Pensions: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent from the public purse on the payment of the state pension to non-UK citizens in each European Economic Area country for each year from 1997-98 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15456"
