"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426714","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Family Test was announced by my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014.</p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills welcomed the introduction of the Family Test and has taken steps to embed it by building it into the Department’s Public Sector Equality Duty commitments. All family test assessments are documented and publication considered where significant impact is identified.</p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance, published by the Department for Work and Pensions -</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><p>As stated in the guidance, there is no requirement to publish Family Test assessments.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","15337","2015-11-23T10:16:38.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426714/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426714/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-06","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many of his Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps he has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15327"
