"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426717","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-13","<p>A consultation on support for postgraduate study was launched in March of this year. The consultation sought views on the Government’s intention to introduce a new loan scheme for taught Master’s study and a review of how to broaden and strengthen support for postgraduate research. Consultation responses have been analysed and the Department is preparing its response.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-13T12:31:21.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426717/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426717/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-06","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what progress his Department has made on introducing loans for postgraduate study.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","15302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426718","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Family Test was announced by my right hon. Friend the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014.</p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills welcomed the introduction of the Family Test and has taken steps to embed it by building it into the Department’s Public Sector Equality Duty commitments. All family test assessments are documented and publication considered where significant impact is identified.</p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance, published by the Department for Work and Pensions -</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><p>As stated in the guidance, there is no requirement to publish Family Test assessments.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","15327","2015-11-23T10:16:38.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426718/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426718/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-06","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426719","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Government is committed to delivering a quicker and more efficient business rates appeals system in England, so that businesses can be confident they are paying the right amount of business rates and any refunds can be paid quickly. Details of our proposals are set out in the consultation paper <em>Check, Challenge, Appeal: Reforming Business Rates Appeals</em>, available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-business-rates-appeals-check-challenge-appeal" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-business-rates-appeals-check-challenge-appeal</a>. Enabling legislation is being taken forward in the Enterprise Bill.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","15285","2015-11-16T13:58:35.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426719/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426719/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-06","Rates and Rating: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with ministerial colleagues on reviewing the Valuation Office Agency process for considering rating assessment appeals.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","15282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426720","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Government is committed to delivering a quicker and more efficient business rates appeals system in England, so that businesses can be confident they are paying the right amount of business rates and any refunds can be paid quickly. Details of our proposals are set out in the consultation paper <em>Check, Challenge, Appeal: Reforming Business Rates Appeals</em>, available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-business-rates-appeals-check-challenge-appeal" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-business-rates-appeals-check-challenge-appeal</a>. Enabling legislation is being taken forward in the Enterprise Bill.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","15282","2015-11-16T13:58:35.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426720/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426720/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-06","Rates and Rating: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had about reducing the time taken by the Valuation Office Agency to consider rating assessment appeals.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","15285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426721","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>Based on data used to publish the latest Official Statistics, the average time taken to resolve a challenge to the rating list is 13 months for the 2005 list and 14 months for the 2010 list.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T15:45:13.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426721/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426721/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Rates and Rating: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average time taken was for a rating assessment appeal to be considered by the Valuation Office Agency in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","15286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426722","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>The information requested can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/non-domestic-rating-challenges-and-changes-experimental" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/non-domestic-rating-challenges-and-changes-experimental</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T17:10:53.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426722/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426722/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Rates and Rating: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many rating assessment appeals are outstanding with the Valuation Office Agency.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","15287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426723","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-13","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and my Department follows that guidance available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","15338","2015-11-13T10:57:39.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426723/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426723/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-06","Cabinet Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many of his Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps he has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426724","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-13","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and my Department follows that guidance available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","15328","2015-11-13T10:57:39.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426724/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426724/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-06","Cabinet Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426725","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>The expected impact over the forecast period of the changes made to private pensions taxation as announced at Budget 2014 can be found in Table 2.1 (p.56) of the Budget 2014 document here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/293759/37630_Budget_2014_Web_Accessible.pdf</a></p><br /><p>Following a consultation period the Chancellor made subsequent announcements relating to this measure. The Exchequer impact of these can be found in Table 2.1 (p.65) of the Autumn Statement 2014 document here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382327/44695_Accessible.pdf</a></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-16T16:22:18.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426725/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426725/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the change in tax revenue as a result of the introduction of new pension freedoms.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","15304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426726","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Financial Policy Committee (FPC) within the Bank of England identifies, monitors and addresses risks to the UK financial system; including overseas exposures.</p><br /><p>The FPC regularly publishes the indicators that it considers when formulating policy, and this includes all countries to which UK banks have large or rapidly growing total exposure. The most recent indicators (for Q2 2015) can be found on the Bank of England’s website using the link below.</p><br /><p>http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/financialstability/Pages/fpc/coreindicators.aspx</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-16T16:23:08.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426726/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426726/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426726/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the vulnerability of the UK banking system to a Russian debt default; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426727","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>This information is available at:</p><br /><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/449343/HMRC_Annual_Report_and_Accounts_2014-15__Web_accessible_version_.pdf</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-11-16T15:40:13.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426727/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426727/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much is owed in overpaid tax credits.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","15239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426728","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>In his speech on Europe on November 10<sup>th</sup>, the Prime Minister reaffirmed the Government’s proposal that people coming to Britain from the EU must live here and contribute for 4 years before they qualify for in work benefits or social housing. This proposal is included in the Prime Minister’s letter to Mr. Tusk.</p><br /><p>DWP’s statistical release from November 10th explained that it is estimated that, at March 2013, between 37 and 45% of the EEA nationals (excluding students) who were resident in the UK having arrived in the preceding 4 years were in households claiming either an in-work or out-of-work benefit or tax credit.</p><p>This represents between 195,000 and 235,000 EEA nationals in recently arrived households claiming benefits or tax credits at March 2013 out of 525,000 recently arrived EEA nationals resident in the UK at March 2013.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-11-16T16:12:12.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426728/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426728/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Welfare Tax Credits: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 2 November 2015 to Question 13969, what information his Department has to help inform policy development on the payment of child and tax credits to foreign nationals.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","15241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426729","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<ol><li>The information requested is as follows: <br><p>2010-11 = 42.6m</p><p>2011-12 = 42.6m</p><p>2012-13 = 42.6m</p><p>2013-14 = 43.7m</p><p>2014-15 = 44.7m</li><li>This information is not held by HMRC.</li></ol>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T15:53:29.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426729/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426729/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","PAYE","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the (a) number of employees paying tax through PAYE and (b) amount paid by such employees on service charges, tips, cover charges and gratuities administered via workplace payrolls for each financial year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","15205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426730","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) did not receive any reports of the online renewal system failing to record and register information submitted by claimants renewing their 2013-14 claim.</p><p><br></p><p>HMRC received one report of the online renewal system failing to record and register information submitted by claimants renewing their 2014-15 claim.</p><br /><p>HMRC do not hold the requested data broken down by Child Tax Credit and Working Tax Credit</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T17:14:01.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426730/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426730/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many reports his Department has received of HM Revenue and Customs' online renewal system failing to record and register information and supporting documentation submitted by claimants wishing to renew their claim for (a) child tax credit and (b) working tax credit in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","15225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426731","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>There are no current plans for ministers to visit the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) office in Cumbernauld. HMRC continues to engage its workforce on its transformation through a series of staff events. Further details of these plans were announced on 12 November.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T15:43:16.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426731/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426731/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Revenue and Customs: Cumbernauld","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will visit the HM Revenue and Customs workforce in Cumbernauld to discuss their long-term employment at the tax centre there.","false","Biography information for John McNally","Falkirk","John Mc Nally","15226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426732","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) already has three units which deal specifically with representations from hon. Members in relation to their constituents’ concerns: a dedicated MP hotline for Tax Credits, an MP complaints team that deals with tax credit complaints, and an HMRC Ministerial correspondence team.</p><br /><p>The dedicated MP hotline is a telephone helpline to assist MPs, MEPs, MSPs, Welsh Assembly Members and their staff when dealing with constituents’ Tax Credit issues. Advisors deal with around 11,500 calls per year.</p><p><br> <br></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-16T15:50:25.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426732/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426732/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-06","Revenue and Customs: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to his Answer of 30 October 2015 to Question 13346, if he will make it his policy to introduce a dedicated team at the tax credit office in Preston constituency to deal with tax credit cases referred to them by hon. Members.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","15228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426733","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>We welcome the opportunity to engage with the supported housing sector to understand how the sector’s views can best be accommodated as we implement our policy. Ministers and officials have been discussing this issue with the National Housing Federation and a number of providers.</p><p>We plan to except specialised supported housing, residential care homes, nursing homes and PFI-funded Extra Care housing from the rent reductions. We are continuing to work with the sector on this issue to ensure the most vulnerable are protected.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-16T14:06:44.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426733/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426733/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-06","Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will meet providers of (a) supported housing and (b) specified housing to discuss the effect of the proposed change to social rents on the viability of those types of housing.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","15201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426734","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-16","<p>Cabinet Office will shortly issue guidance that reminds public authorities of their international obligations when letting public contracts. Foreign policy is not a matter for local authorities. The guidance will make clear that boycotts in public procurement are inappropriate and may be illegal, outside where formal legal sanctions, embargoes and restrictions that have been put in place by the Government.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","15223","2015-11-16T11:12:04.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426734/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426734/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-06","Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how he plans to implement his policy on local authority procurement policies in relation to boycotts, divestments and sanctions against other countries and the UK defence industry announced on 3 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","15207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426735","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>DCLG Ministers attended the following Diwali functions:</p><br /><p><strong>2014:</strong></p><p>The All-Party Parliamentary Group for British Hindus at the House of Commons (15 October 2014) - Rt. Hon. Eric Pickles MP</p><p>Deputy Prime Minister’s Diwali function at Admiralty House (22 October 2014) - Stephen Williams MP</p><p>Conservative Party event to celebrate Diwali at the Queen Elizabeth II Conference Centre (27 October 2014) - Rt. Hon. Eric Pickles MP</p><br /><p><strong>2015:</strong></p><p>Prime Minister's Diwali reception at No10 Downing Street (10 November 2015) - Rt. Hon. Greg Clark MP and Baroness Williams of Trafford</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-11-16T13:28:30.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426735/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426735/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-06","Department for Communities and Local Government: Diwali","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which Diwali celebrations he, his predecessor or Ministers in his Department attended in 2014 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","15197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426736","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-16","<p>Cabinet Office will shortly issue guidance that reminds public authorities of their international obligations when letting public contracts. Foreign policy is not a matter for local authorities. The guidance will make clear that boycotts in public procurement are inappropriate and may be illegal, outside where formal legal sanctions, embargoes and restrictions that have been put in place by the Government.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","15207","2015-11-16T11:12:04.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426736/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426736/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-06","Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions he had with the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs when developing his Department's policy on local authority procurement policies and companies' investment and divestment decisions announced on 3 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","15223"
