"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426744","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>My Department does not hold this information.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-11-16T13:30:33.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426744/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426744/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426744/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-06","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of references of families to the Troubled Families programme have been the result of schools expressing concerns that children are not receiving sufficient food at home since April 2015.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","15326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426745","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. DWP published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and my Department follows that guidance-<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p><br>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-16T14:38:40.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426745/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426745/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-06","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many of his Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps he has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426746","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. DWP published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and my Department follows that guidance-<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p><br>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-16T14:39:41.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426746/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426746/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-06","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15340"
