"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426748","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-20","<p>Government ministers were in attendance at the Prime Minister's Diwali reception at No 10 Downing Street to celebrate the biggest festival in the Hindu calendar. Due to prior diary commitments, DCMS ministers were unable to attend Diwali celebrations this year in their official capacity.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-20T12:08:56.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426748/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426748/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-06","Diwali","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which Diwali celebrations he, his predecessor or Ministers in his Department attended in 2014 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","15196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426749","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><p>No aircraft owned by the Armed Forces are leased to private businesses.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T16:33:40.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426749/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426749/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many aircraft owned by each service branch of the armed forces are leased to private businesses; and how much is paid to each such branch in respect of such leases.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","15199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426750","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The UK Armed Forces have a distinguished history of serving with great courage and professionalism in a wide-range of conflict situations; over the years various foreign military awards have been approved for acceptance and some of these have also been approved for wearing. A full list of the qualifying criteria for, and permission to wear, campaign medals, foreign medals and medals awarded by international organisations is available in Joint Service Publication 761 which can be found at the following website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/396186/JSP761_honours_awards.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/396186/JSP761_honours_awards.pdf</a></p><br /><p>Information on the numbers of UK Service personnel or veterans who have been awarded the NATO Africa Medal is not held by the Ministry of Defence as this is administered by NATO.</p><br /><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","15240","2015-11-16T16:49:48.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426750/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426750/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 2 November 2015 to Question 13951, which foreign military awards have been approved for members of the UK armed forces to wear; and what criteria are applied in determining such approval.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","15238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426751","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The UK Armed Forces have a distinguished history of serving with great courage and professionalism in a wide-range of conflict situations; over the years various foreign military awards have been approved for acceptance and some of these have also been approved for wearing. A full list of the qualifying criteria for, and permission to wear, campaign medals, foreign medals and medals awarded by international organisations is available in Joint Service Publication 761 which can be found at the following website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/396186/JSP761_honours_awards.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/396186/JSP761_honours_awards.pdf</a></p><br /><p>Information on the numbers of UK Service personnel or veterans who have been awarded the NATO Africa Medal is not held by the Ministry of Defence as this is administered by NATO.</p><br /><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","15238","2015-11-16T16:49:48.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426751/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426751/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","NATO: Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) current and (b) former members of the UK armed forces have been awarded the NATO Africa Medal.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","15240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426752","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>It has not been possible in the time available to provide a geographical breakdown of projected estimated civilian personnel strengths by Top Level Budget. Ministry of Defence (MOD) officials will investigate what information can be provided and I will write in due course.</p><p>As at 1 July 2015 the MOD employed 3,770 civilian personnel at locations in Scotland. A breakdown by Unitary Authority can be found in the Quarterly Locations Report, the latest edition of which can be found at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/location-of-uk-regular-service-and-civilian-personnel-quarterly-statistics-2015</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-11-16T17:09:06.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426752/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426752/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Ministry of Defence: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 30 October 2015 to Question 14252, what estimate he has made of his Department's likely strength of civilian personnel based in Scotland on 1 April (a) 2016 and (b) 2020 for each top level budget.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","15230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426753","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><br /><p>Over the past 10 years, UK military personnel have been deployed to a number of UN mandated peacekeeping missions including: Cyprus (UNFICYP), Mali (MINUSMA), South Sudan (UNMISS), Democratic Republic of Congo (MONUSCO), Liberia (UNMIL), Dafur (UNAMID), UNAMI (IRAQ), UNIOSIL (Sierra Leone), UNMIK (Kosovo), UNOMIG (Georgia), UNMIN (Nepal), UNAMA (Afghanistan), UNSOM (Somalia) and UNSMIL (Libya/Tunisia).</p><br /><p>The number of military personnel who have deployed on the various UN operations is set out below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>2006*</p></td><td><p>2007*</p></td><td><p>2008*</p></td><td><p>2009*</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015**</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total number of UK personnel deployed per year</p></td><td><p><br>295</p></td><td><p><br>290</p></td><td><p><br>301</p></td><td><p><br>293</p></td><td><p><br>279</p></td><td><p><br>276</p></td><td><p><br>280</p></td><td><p><br>278</p></td><td><p><br>285</p></td><td><p><br>287</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>* The details supplied are correct as of 31 January each year.</p><p>** Correct as of 10 November 2015.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-11-16T16:35:06.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426753/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426753/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","United Nations: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK personnel have served in UN peacekeeping missions in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","15232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426754","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><p>The first three Astute class submarines were ordered as a single batch. Separate construction costs for Artful are, therefore, not held by the department. As such, it is not possible to determine how much the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has spent on HMS Artful individually; nor what the MOD expected the specific cost of HMS Artful to be, when commissioned.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","15753","2015-11-16T16:27:08.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426754/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426754/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","HMS Artful","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on HMS Artful.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426755","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>It is planned that Artful will be handed over to the Royal Navy in December 2015. I cannot comment on when Artful will be deployed on active service as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T16:49:07.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426755/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426755/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","HMS Artful","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when HMS Artful is planned to be in active service.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426756","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) is looking across the spectrum to assess what defence capabilities will address the threats we face. The conclusions of the SDSR are due to be published on 23 November.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T17:10:02.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426756/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426756/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Trafalgar Class Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans the Government has for the decommissioning of (a) HMS Torbay, (b) HMS Trenchant, (c) HMS Talent and (d) HMS Triumph.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426757","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The safety of the UK submarine fleet is of paramount importance. The Ministry of Defence assesses seaworthiness for submarines through a robust sea clearance process. This assessment is kept under continuous review.</p><p>I am withholding the seaworthiness state of each submarine as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","15289","2015-11-16T16:27:52.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426757/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426757/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Trafalgar Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the seaworthiness is of (a) HMS Torbay, (b) HMS Trenchant, (c) HMS Talent and (d) HMS Triumph.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426758","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>In accordance with international law as set out in the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS), Royal Navy warships exercise the right of innocent passage whenever transiting in another States' recognised territorial seas. The exercise of the right of innocent passage requires neither prior authorization nor authorization from the coastal State. When operating in the Exclusive Economic Zone of a coastal State, RN warships will exercise full freedom of navigation and overflight whilst respecting any established safety zones, up to 500 meters, around an artificial island, installation or structure.</p><p>In the South China Sea the UK has a strong interest in the maintenance of peace and stability, which is underpinned by respect for, and adherence to, international law<em>.</em> The UK strongly supports its right, and that of all States, to exercise freedom of navigation in accordance with UNCLOS. We urge all States to respect these very important rights.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-11-16T16:30:15.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426758/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426758/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Spratly Islands: Territorial Waters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Royal Navy plans to adhere to the 12-nautical mile territorial limit proclaimed by China around the Subi and Mischief reefs in the Spratly archipelago; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426759","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><br /><p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. The Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and the Ministry of Defence (MOD) follows that guidance: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><br /><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that Departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p><br /><br /><p>Over the last five years the MOD has significantly increased the support provided to the families of Service personnel. For details of these I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 9 June 2015 to Question 1192 to the hon. Member for Enfield Southgate (Mr Burrowes): <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-04/1192/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-04/1192/</a></p><br /><p>Since I provided that answer I was delighted to announce to the Confederation of Service Charities (COBSEO) Annual General Meeting on 30 September our plans for the first UK Armed Forces Families Strategy, the aim of which is to provide a clearer focus for our efforts to understand, value and empower the families of our Armed Forces personnel. This Strategy will build on the successes outlined in my answer by addressing inconsistencies and incoherence in MOD policies and by improving our communications to Armed Forces families.</p><br /><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","15331 ; 15350","2015-11-16T16:29:33.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426759/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426759/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Ministry of Defence: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426760","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><br /><p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. The Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and the Ministry of Defence (MOD) follows that guidance: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><br /><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance. While the guidance states that Departments should consider publishing assessments carried out under the Test, there is no requirement to do so.</p><br /><br /><p>Over the last five years the MOD has significantly increased the support provided to the families of Service personnel. For details of these I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 9 June 2015 to Question 1192 to the hon. Member for Enfield Southgate (Mr Burrowes): <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-04/1192/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-04/1192/</a></p><br /><p>Since I provided that answer I was delighted to announce to the Confederation of Service Charities (COBSEO) Annual General Meeting on 30 September our plans for the first UK Armed Forces Families Strategy, the aim of which is to provide a clearer focus for our efforts to understand, value and empower the families of our Armed Forces personnel. This Strategy will build on the successes outlined in my answer by addressing inconsistencies and incoherence in MOD policies and by improving our communications to Armed Forces families.</p><br /><br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","15341 ; 15350","2015-11-16T16:29:33.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426760/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426760/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Ministry of Defence: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of his Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps he has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426761","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The cost of maintenance onboard submarines is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T16:30:56.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426761/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426761/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Trafalgar Class Submarines: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on maintenance aboard HMS (a) Torbay, (b) Trenchant, (c) Talent and (d) Triumph in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426762","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<p>The safety of the UK submarine fleet is of paramount importance. The Ministry of Defence assesses seaworthiness for submarines through a robust sea clearance process. This assessment is kept under continuous review.</p><p>I am withholding the seaworthiness state of each submarine as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","15295","2015-11-16T16:27:52.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426762/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426762/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Astute Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the seaworthiness is of HMS (a) Astute and (b) Ambush.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426763","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-11","<p>Training onboard Royal Navy Submarines is a continual process with specific Command courses for submarine Captains and organised training for replacement Officers and Other Ranks by suitably qualified and experienced personnel.</p><p>Identifying all those personnel who have undertaken any aspect of training on these vessels could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-11-11T13:59:40.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426763/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426763/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Astute Class Submarines: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel have been trained aboard HMS (a) Astute and (b) Ambush.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426764","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-16","<br /><p>The process for reporting and assessing deficiencies against the material state of a submarine does not use the definition of a fault. The material state of a submarine is formally assessed at the end of each maintenance period. In the time in between maintenance periods, Ship's Staff report changes to this assessed material state using the Operational Defect reporting process.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-16T16:26:19.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426764/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426764/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-06","Astute Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many faults have been found aboard HMS (a) Astute, (b) Ambush and (c) Artful since it left dry dock.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","15291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426765","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>The family test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. The Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy which can be found online[1]. The Department for Education follows this guidance.</p><p>The family test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policies in line with the family test guidance.</p><p>As stated in the guidance, there is no requirement to publish family test assessments. The Department has published the outcome of such assessments on a number of occasions, including as part of the impact assessments of the Childcare Bill[2] and the Education and Adoption Bill[3].</p><br /><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/family-test-assessing-the-impact-of-policies-on-families" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/family-test-assessing-the-impact-of-policies-on-families</a></p><p>[2] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/childcare-bill-impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/childcare-bill-impact-assessment</a></p><p>[3] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/education-and-adoption-bill-impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/education-and-adoption-bill-impact-assessment</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","15342","2015-11-16T16:39:18.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426765/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426765/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Department for Education: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many of her Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps she has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426766","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>The family test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014. The Department for Work and Pensions published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy which can be found online[1]. The Department for Education follows this guidance.</p><p>The family test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policies in line with the family test guidance.</p><p>As stated in the guidance, there is no requirement to publish family test assessments. The Department has published the outcome of such assessments on a number of occasions, including as part of the impact assessments of the Childcare Bill[2] and the Education and Adoption Bill[3].</p><br /><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/family-test-assessing-the-impact-of-policies-on-families" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/family-test-assessing-the-impact-of-policies-on-families</a></p><p>[2] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/childcare-bill-impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/childcare-bill-impact-assessment</a></p><p>[3] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/education-and-adoption-bill-impact-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/education-and-adoption-bill-impact-assessment</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","15332","2015-11-16T16:39:19.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426766/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426766/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Department for Education: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426767","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>The latest historical information on recruitment of new initial teacher trainees can be found in the ITT Census online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-teacher-training" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-teacher-training</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-11-16T17:52:43.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426767/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426767/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 5 November 2015 to Question 14021, how many new teachers were trained in each of the last 10 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","15281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426768","Department for Education","false","2015-11-12","<p>The Department for Education uses the Teacher Supply Model (TSM) to estimate the demand for qualified teachers in active service within state-funded schools in England each year using a range of assumptions including projections for the numbers of pupils in schools. The TSM then estimates the number of postgraduate Initial Teacher Training (ITT) places required in England to meet this demand, given the number of entrants expected through routes other than the Newly Qualified Teacher route; for example through returning to teaching.</p><br /><p>The TSM estimates the number of postgraduate training places required one year in advance and is updated each year to take account of the most up-to-date data – for example, the population projections published by the Office of National Statistics (ONS) - which means our estimates change each year. As with any long-term forecast, the further into the future the forecast the more uncertain the estimates become. For this reason, the department does not produce 25 year forecasts of teacher demand. The forecast period of the current TSM provides the department with estimates of the broad trend in likely future demand for teachers which is sufficient for our policy development needs.</p><br /><p>The 2016/17 version of the TSM, which was used to inform the 2016/17 ITT recruitment process, along with a user guide explaining the methodology in detail, is available at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-supply-model" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-supply-model</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-11-12T17:12:41.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426768/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426768/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will make an estimate of the number of additional teachers that will be needed to accommodate the predicted population rise over the next 25 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426769","Department for Education","false","2015-11-12","<p>Schools have a key role to play in teaching children about healthy lifestyles.</p><br /><p>The new national curriculum set the expectation that pupils are taught about the importance of leading healthy and active lives, across a variety of subjects. The new design and technology curriculum strengthens requirements for maintained schools to teach children about food, nutrition and healthy eating, and how to cook a repertoire of meals. Pupils in maintained primary schools should learn about healthy eating and a good, balanced diet. In maintained secondary schools, food education is now compulsory in years 7–9 for the first time. The new science curriculum makes young people aware of different types of diseases and the impact of lifestyle factors on the incidence of some diseases.</p><br /><p>Physical Education is a compulsory subject at all four key stages in the national curriculum in maintained schools. The programme of study makes clear that a high-quality PE curriculum should provide opportunities for pupils to become physically active in a way which supports their health and fitness.</p><br /><p>In addition, the Department is actively engaged in work across government to develop a national childhood obesity strategy.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-11-12T17:19:28.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426769/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426769/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Health Education: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to improve health literacy among children; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","15252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426770","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>Pupil forecasts based on ONS population projections have been made out to 2024 and they suggest that pupil numbers are due to rise significantly over that period. Local authorities are responsible for ensuring that there are sufficient schools to meet that need, and for determining precisely how many new schools are needed in their area.</p><p>We allocate funding for new school places to local authorities three years in advance in order to balance the need for robust forecasts and to ensure certainty for local authorities over their future funding allocations.</p><p>Providing this funding to support local authorities in creating additional school places is one of the Government’s top priorities. This is signalled by the £7 billion that this Government has committed to spend on new places over the course of this Parliament; as well as the £5 billion that the previous Coalition Government invested in school places between 2011 and 2015 (more than double the £1.9 billion spent between 2007 and 2011).</p><br />","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-11-16T17:49:37.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426770/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426770/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-06","Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will make an estimate of the number of additional schools that will be needed to accommodate the predicted population rise over the next 25 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","15261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426771","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him today to Question 14997.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-13T12:21:56.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426771/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426771/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Solar Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate her Department has made of the likely market size of the UK solar industry in 2016.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","15189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426772","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-16","<p>The FIT review consultation was published on 27 August and closed on 23 October. The review proposed changes to generation tariffs and tariff bands and included proposals on cost control measures, such as capping deployment, in order to put the scheme onto an affordable and sustainable footing. An option to close the scheme, should cost control measures not be sufficient to achieve this, was also set out in the consultation.</p><br /><p>We have received nearly 55,000 responses to the consultation. We are currently analysing these responses and will do so as quickly as possible. We will publish a Government response in due course.</p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-16T14:24:57.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426772/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426772/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Renewable Energy: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she plans to close the feed-in tariff scheme in January 2016; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","15202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426773","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-16","<p>We have received nearly 55,000 responses. We currently estimate that just over 2,600 are unique and detailed responses; the rest are briefer and more uniform responses, generated by campaigns. We will assess and evaluate all responses and will respond in due course.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-16T14:14:04.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426773/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426773/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Renewable Energy: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many responses her Department received to the recent consultation on a review of the feed-in tariff scheme.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","15203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426774","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-11","<p>On 4 November 2015, the Government set out proposals to ensure that hydraulic fracturing cannot be conducted from wells drilled at the surface of specified protected areas.<sup>1</sup> The proposed restrictions would be delivered through the inclusion of a licence condition in new Petroleum Exploration and Development Licences (PEDLs) and the development of a policy statement designed to inform the approval process for programmes submitted for approval under existing PEDLs.</p><br /><p>The proposals are now subject to consultation with key stakeholders, including the industry and non-governmental organisations.</p><br /><p><em><strong>[1]</strong></em><em> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/oil-and-gas-licensing-rounds#surface-development-restrictions" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/oil-and-gas-licensing-rounds#surface-development-restrictions</a> </em></p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-11T16:35:00.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426774/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426774/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she plans to bring forward legislative proposals that hydraulic fracturing cannot be conducted from wells that are drilled at the surface of sensitive areas.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","15221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426775","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-16","<p>I will be writing to hon. Members who have signed EDM 619, in which I will respond to the objection. I will deposit a copy of the response in the Libraries of the House.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-16T14:13:00.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426775/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426775/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Hinkley Point C Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will establish an examination of objections to her departmental minute of 21 October 2015 including the entering into contracts regarding the Hinkley Point C power station that could give rise to liabilities.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","15222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426776","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-25","<p>Coal accounted for 39% of total UK electricity generation in 2012, falling to 30% in 2014. This trend is expected to continue and the Department’s published forecasts suggest that, in our central scenario, the last unabated UK coal fired power station will close in 2026.</p><br /><p>However, if market conditions are right, there is a possibility that coal could continue to produce electricity until the late 2020s.</p><br /><p><em>Source: DECC Updated energy and emissions projections 2014 <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368021/Updated_energy_and_emissions_projections2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368021/Updated_energy_and_emissions_projections2014.pdf</a></em></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-25T16:57:33.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426776/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426776/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Coal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether it is Government policy to phase out coal.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","15246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426777","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Family Test was announced by my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister in August 2014, and introduced in October 2014. DWP published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and the Department follows that guidance:</p><br /><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf.</p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance.</p><br /><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><br /><p>DECC has not applied the Test to date but is considering where it is appropriate to do so. In addition where relevant, DECC already publishes in Impact Assessments analysis of the impact of policies on energy bills across different types of households.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","15333","2015-11-16T14:13:32.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426777/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426777/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Department of Energy and Climate Change: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department is taking to implement the family test.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426778","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Family Test was announced by my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister in August 2014, and introduced in October 2014. DWP published guidance for Departments and officials on how the test should be applied when formulating policy and the Department follows that guidance:</p><br /><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf.</p><p>The Family Test is an integral part of the policy making process and is applied in a proportionate way in the development of all new policy in line with the Family Test guidance.</p><br /><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><br /><p>DECC has not applied the Test to date but is considering where it is appropriate to do so. In addition where relevant, DECC already publishes in Impact Assessments analysis of the impact of policies on energy bills across different types of households.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","15343","2015-11-16T14:13:32.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426778/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426778/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-06","Department of Energy and Climate Change: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many of her Department's policies have been assessed against the family test; what steps she has taken to publish the outcome of such assessments that have been carried out; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","15333"
